        public static boolean parseCharRef​(java.lang.String input,

        Parameters:

        ref - The reference character for the input to be checked against.
        Returns:

      • parseColor

        public static javafx.scene.paint.Paint parseColor​(java.lang.String colorStr)
        Creates JavaFX Paint object representing the color given with its string name, or MATLAB color abbreviation. Accepted colors: red (r), green (g), blue (b), black (k), yellow (y), cyan (c), magenta (m).
        Parameters:
        colorStr - String representation of a color.
        Returns:
        color as JavaFX Paint object.

      • parseHex

        Parameters:
        colorStr - hex code of an RGB encoded color as String.
        Returns:
        color as JavaFX Paint object.
